headline: Why International Paper (IP) Stock Is Down Today
summary: Shares of packaging and materials company International Paper (NYSE:IP) fell 10.7% in the morning session after the company reported disappointing third-quarter 2025 results that missed analyst expectations on both revenue and profit.

headline: International Paper reverses 2025 box shipment expectations
summary: Although box shipments ticked up in September and early October, full-year volumes are now expected to be down, executives said on Thursday’s earnings call. They also discussed recently announced closures.

headline: International Paper (NYSE:IP) Reports Sales Below Analyst Estimates In Q3 Earnings, Stock Drops
summary: Packaging and materials company International Paper (NYSE:IP) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales rose 32.8% year on year to $6.22 billion. Its non-GAAP loss of $0.43 per share was significantly below analysts’ consensus estimates.
